<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Large <rs type="material" key="marmor">blue marble</rs>   <rs type="objectType">laver</rs> partly reconstructed from fragments (<measure type="length" dim="diameter" precision="circa">2.75</measure> across cord) with central boss (<measure type="length" dim="diameter" precision="circa">0.87</measure> across cord).</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the boss. There is a pair, broken, and too damaged to show whether it also was inscribed.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p>Very worn;  <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.095</measure>.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
 <head>Date</head>

<p> <date exact="none" notBefore="0101" notAfter="0300">Second to third centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, especially four-bar <foreign lang="grc">Σ</foreign> in ll. 3, 4).</p></div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>

<ab><lb n="1"/><gap dim="left" extent="2" reason="lost" unit="character"/><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">λ</unclear>υ</orig><gap dim="internal" extent="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">ε</unclear></orig><lb n="2"/><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">τ</unclear>ι</orig><gap dim="internal" extent="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">ωι</unclear></orig><gap dim="right" extent="3" reason="lost" unit="line"/><lb n="3"/><w lemma="ὁ">τοὺς</w>  <w lemma="δύο">δύ<unclear reason="damage">ω</unclear></w><lb n="4"/><w lemma="λουτήρ"><unclear reason="damage">λο</unclear>υτῆρας</w><lb n="5"/><w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκε</w></ab>
</div>

<div type="apparatus"><head>Apparatus</head><p>ll. 1, 2, the name and presumably patronymic are too badly damaged to yield sense.</p></div><div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Transcription (Reynolds).</p>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p><gap dim="left" reason="lost" unit="character"/> dedicated the two lavers.</p></div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>Mentioned by <bibl><author>Reynolds</author>, <title level="j">Aphrodisias Papers</title> I, 39</bibl>. These lavers possibly belonged originally in the gymnasium mentioned on the architrave <xref type="inscription" n="1253" href="010174">1.174</xref> (=Temple 12).</p>
</div>

<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Temple/Church</rs>: atrium</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Unknown</rs>. Last recorded: <rs type="lastLocation">Findspot (1980)</rs></p>
</div>





